title: Fronta
text:
The Diocese of Fronta () is a suppressed and <a href="titular%20see">titular see</a> of the <a href="Roman%20Catholic%20Church">Roman Catholic Church</a>.
During the <a href="Roman%20Empire">Roman Empire</a> the Diocese of Fronta, was of the <a href="Roman%20province">Roman province</a> of <a href="Mauretania%20Caesariensis">Mauretania Caesariensis</a>. The location of the <a href="cathedra">seat</a> of the <a href="diocese">diocese</a> remains unknown but has been tentatively identified with Fortassa, <a href="Uz%C3%A8s-le-Duc">Uzès-le-Duc</a> in modern <a href="Algeria">Algeria</a>. The only known <a href="bishop">bishop</a> of this diocese from <a href="late%20antiquity">antiquity</a> is Donato, who took part in the <a href="Council%20of%20Carthage%20%28484%29">synod assembled in Carthage in 484</a> by the <a href="Vandal">Vandal</a> King <a href="Huneric">Huneric</a>, after which the bishop was exiled.
Today Fronta survives as a <a href="titular%20bishop">titular bishop</a>ric and the current bishop is <a href="Josef%20Gr%C3%BCnwald">Josef Grünwald</a>, of <a href="Augsburg">Augsburg</a>.
